description: Tudor Gold Corp., a junior resource exploration company, engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral properties in Canada. The company primarily explores for gold, copper, silver, precious, and other base metals. The Company's flagship project is the Treaty Creek property covering an area of approximately 17,130 hectares located in the Golden Triangle area to the north of Stewart, British Columbia, Canada. It also holds a 100% interest in the Crown project and the Eskay North project, which are located in the Golden Triangle area. Tudor Gold Corp. is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Kenneth  Konkin P. Geo., P.Geo.
